## 6. Layer 5 вҖ” TURN Layer (coturn)

### 6.1 Regional Topology

**Existing implementation:** [coturn-deployment.yaml](file:///d:/projects/social/k8s/coturn-deployment.yaml), [turn.service.ts](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/modules/call/turn.service.ts)

```
в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ Per Region в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ  NLB (UDP:3478, TCP:5349)                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ                                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ coturn-01 в”Ӯ в”Ӯ coturn-02в”Ӯ в”Ӯ coturn-N в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ UDP:3478  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ UDP:3478 в”Ӯ в”Ӯ UDP:3478 в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ TLS:5349  в”Ӯ в”Ӯ TLS:5349 в”Ӯ в”Ӯ TLS:5349 в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ 10Gbps NW в”Ӯ в”Ӯ 10Gbps   в”Ӯ в”Ӯ 10Gbps   в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  HPA: 20 min вҶ’ 200 max (turn_active_allocations)  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  Instance: c6gn.2xlarge (8vCPU, 16GB, 25Gbps NW)  в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
 Г— 4 regions
```

### 6.2 Sizing Per Region

| Metric | Baseline | Peak |
|--------|----------|------|
| TURN nodes | 20 | 200 |
| Concurrent relayed sessions | 75K | 750K |
| Bandwidth per node | 5 Gbps avg | 10 Gbps cap |
| Total regional bandwidth | 100 Gbps | 2 Tbps |

**Math**: ~15-20% of 3M concurrent calls require TURN = ~500K TURN sessions globally Г· 4 regions = ~125K/region at peak.

### 6.3 Ephemeral TURN Credentials (HMAC-SHA1)

```typescript
// From turn.service.ts вҖ” credentials compatible with coturn's use-auth-secret
const timestamp = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) + 86400; // 24h TTL
const username = `${timestamp}:${userId}`;
const credential = crypto.createHmac('sha1', TURN_SECRET).update(username).digest('base64');

return {
  urls: [
    `stun:${turnDomain}:3478`,
    `turn:${turnDomain}:3478?transport=udp`,     // UDP first
    `turn:${turnDomain}:3478?transport=tcp`,     // TCP fallback
    `turns:${turnDomain}:5349?transport=tcp`,    // TLS last resort
  ],
  username, credential, ttl: 86400,
};
```

### 6.4 Geo-Based TURN Selection

```
Same-region call:    Both users вҶ’ local region's TURN
Cross-region call:   Compare turn:load:{region} вҶ’ select lower load
Both overloaded:     selectLeastLoaded() across all 4 regions (circuit breaker)
```

### 6.5 TURN Overload Prevention

| Mechanism | Implementation |
|-----------|---------------|
| Per-user bandwidth cap | `max-bps=2000000` (2 Mbps/allocation) |
| Total quota per node | `total-quota=1000` allocations |
| Per-user allocation limit | Max 2 concurrent (Redis `turn:alloc:{userId}`) |
| Health-based routing | NLB removes unhealthy nodes in <10s |
| Autoscaling trigger | HPA: scale up when `allocations/max > 0.7` |
| Circuit breaker | If all nodes >90% вҶ’ spill to adjacent region |
| UDP-first optimization | `iceCandidatePoolSize: 10`, UDP candidates prioritized |

