```

### 9.2 State Definitions & TTLs

| State | TTL | Description |
|-------|-----|-------------|
| `IDLE` | вҖ” | User not in any call |
| `INITIATING` | 10s | Pre-flight checks (auth, block, rate limit, spam) |
| `SIGNALING` | 15s | Routing `call:incoming` to target user |
| `RINGING` | 30s | Target device is ringing |
| `ACCEPTED` | 15s | Target accepted, preparing WebRTC |
| `REJECTED` | 5s | Target declined (terminal) |
| `TIMEOUT` | 5s | Ring timeout exceeded (terminal) |
| `CONNECTING` | 20s | SDP offer/answer exchange |
| `ICE_NEGOTIATION` | 30s | ICE candidate gathering/exchange |
| `AUDIO_ONLY_CONNECTED` | 7200s | Active P2P audio media flowing |
| `VIDEO_CONNECTED` | 7200s | Active P2P audio+video media flowing |
| `VIDEO_UPGRADING` | 15s | Mid-call audioвҶ’video upgrade in progress |
| `DEGRADED` | 7200s | Connected but quality below threshold |
| `RECONNECTING` | 30s | ICE restart in progress |
| `FAILED` | 10s | Unrecoverable failure (terminal) |
| `ENDED` | 10s | Normal termination (terminal) |
| `MISSED` | 5s | Caller hung up before answer (terminal) |
| `REGION_FAILOVER` | 60s | Region failure, migrating signaling |

### 9.3 Race Condition Handling

**Double-Accept Prevention:** Lua CAS script вҖ” only transitions RINGINGвҶ’ACCEPTED atomically.

**Simultaneous Call Detection:** Canonicalized lock key `lock:call:{sorted_u1}:{sorted_u2}` with Redlock 30s TTL.

**Concurrent Upgrade Conflict:** Only one `VIDEO_UPGRADING` transition allowed at a time per call. Second request returns `UPGRADE_IN_PROGRESS`.

**Network Change Detection:** Client heartbeat every 30s. If 2 consecutive heartbeats missed (60s), call forced to ENDED by auditor.

**Device Switching:** On `call:accept` from one device, emit `CALL_HANDLED_ELSEWHERE` to all other device sockets. Priority: mobile > web > tablet.

**Existing implementation:** [call.state-machine.ts](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/modules/call/call.state-machine.ts), [call.coordinator.ts](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/modules/call/call.coordinator.ts)

---

## 10. Voice Calling вҖ” Audio-Only Optimized Path

### 10.1 Audio-Only SDP Negotiation

Audio-only calls use a leaner SDP with **no video m-line**, reducing SDP size by ~40% and eliminating unnecessary ICE candidate gathering for video.

```
SDP Offer (audio-only):
  m=audio 9 UDP/TLS/RTP/SAVPF 111
  a=rtpmap:111 opus/48000/2
  a=fmtp:111 minptime=10;useinbandfec=1;stereo=0;cbr=0;maxaveragebitrate=32000
  a=rtcp-fb:111 transport-cc
  a=extmap:1 urn:ietf:params:rtp-hdrext:ssrc-audio-level
  a=extmap:2 http://www.ietf.org/id/draft-holmer-rmcat-transport-wide-cc-extensions-01
```

### 10.2 Opus Codec Optimization

| Network Quality | Opus Mode | Bitrate | Packet Time | FEC |
|----------------|-----------|---------|-------------|-----|
| Excellent (>1Mbps, <50ms RTT) | VBR | 48-64 kbps | 20ms | Off |
| Good (500kbps-1Mbps) | VBR | 32-48 kbps | 20ms | On |
| Fair (200-500kbps) | CBR | 24-32 kbps | 40ms | On |
| Poor (<200kbps) | CBR | 12-16 kbps | 60ms | On |
| Critical (<100kbps) | CBR | 6-8 kbps | 60ms | On, DTX enabled |

**Silence Detection (DTX):** When enabled, Opus transmits comfort noise during silence periods, reducing bandwidth by ~80% during pauses in conversation.

### 10.3 Audio-Only Performance Advantages

| Metric | Audio-Only | Video Call | Advantage |
|--------|-----------|-----------|-----------|
| SDP size | ~1.2KB | ~3.5KB | 66% smaller |
| ICE candidates | 4-6 | 8-12 | 50% fewer |
| Call setup latency | ~80ms | ~120ms | 33% faster |
| TURN bandwidth | 40 kbps | 800 kbps | 95% less |
| TURN cost per hour | $0.018 | $0.36 | 95% cheaper |
| Battery drain | Low | High | Significant |

### 10.4 Voice-First Failover Logic

When a video call's bandwidth drops below 200kbps for >5 seconds:
1. `CallQualityService.shouldFallbackToAudio()` returns `true`
2. Coordinator emits `CALL_QUALITY_DEGRADED` with `shouldFallbackToAudio: true`
3. Client disables video track, renegotiates SDP to audio-only
4. State transitions: `VIDEO_CONNECTED` вҶ’ `DEGRADED` вҶ’ `AUDIO_ONLY_CONNECTED`

