```

### 11.2 Packet Loss Recovery Strategy

| Packet Loss | Strategy |
|------------|---------|
| 0-2% | No action (normal variance) |
| 2-5% | Enable NACK (retransmission requests) |
| 5-10% | Enable FEC (forward error correction), reduce resolution |
| 10-20% | Aggressive resolution downgrade, increase keyframe frequency |
| >20% | Fallback to audio-only |

### 11.3 Seamless Camera Enable/Disable

Mid-session camera toggle does **not** require SDP renegotiation:
- **Disable**: `videoTrack.enabled = false` вҖ” stops sending video frames, RTP stream paused
- **Enable**: `videoTrack.enabled = true` вҖ” resumes, receiver shows video within 1 keyframe interval (~2s)
- If track was fully removed: requires `addTrack()` + SDP renegotiation (triggers `VIDEO_UPGRADING` state)

