## 14. ICE Candidate Negotiation at Global Scale

### 14.1 ICE Candidate Buffering

When ICE candidates arrive before remote description is set (out-of-order), they are buffered in Redis:

```
call state == CONNECTING вҶ’ buffer in Redis list ice:{callId}:buffer (TTL 60s)
call state == ICE_NEGOTIATION вҶ’ forward immediately via Redis pub/sub
On SDP answer relay вҶ’ flush buffer: LRANGE + DEL + publish each candidate
```

### 14.2 Global ICE Optimization

| Scenario | ICE Strategy |
|----------|-------------|
| Same city | host candidates likely succeed; STUN not needed |
| Same region, different ISP | srflx candidates via STUN; P2P ~80% success |
| Cross-region | srflx may fail; TURN relay likely needed |
| Symmetric NAT (mobile carrier) | TURN relay required (~20% of mobile calls) |

**`iceCandidatePoolSize: 10`** вҖ” Pre-allocates ICE candidate gathering resources before `createOffer()`, reducing setup time by ~30ms.

