## 15. Distributed Presence Strategy

### 15.1 Architecture

**Existing implementation:** [presence.service.ts](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/modules/presence/presence.service.ts), [presence.federation.ts](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/modules/presence/presence.federation.ts)

```
LOCAL: presence:{userId} вҶ’ Redis hash (TTL 120s, heartbeat every 30s)
GLOBAL: gpresence:{userId} вҶ’ Kafka compacted topic вҶ’ materialized in each region's Redis
CARDINALITY: region:users:{region} вҶ’ HyperLogLog
```

### 15.2 Multi-Device Presence

- `presence:{userId}:web`, `presence:{userId}:mobile`
- Call routing priority: **mobile > web > tablet** (user-configurable)
- On accept from one device вҶ’ `CALL_HANDLED_ELSEWHERE` to all others

---

## 16. Multi-Region Active-Active Deployment

### 16.1 Per-Region Stack

Each of the 4 regions runs independently:
- WS Gateway pods (50-500)
- Redis Cluster (6 nodes, 3 shards)
- PostgreSQL (regional instance)
- Kafka cluster (regional, MirrorMaker 2 for cross-region)
- coturn cluster (20-200 nodes)

### 16.2 User-to-Region Affinity

```typescript
// Priority: explicit setting > last-login geo > registration geo
function determineHomeRegion(user): Region {
  if (user.regionAffinity) return user.regionAffinity;
  return GEO_TO_REGION_MAP[geoip.lookup(user.lastLoginIp)] || 'us-east';
}
```

**Existing implementation:** [region.ts](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/config/region.ts)

---

## 17. Security & Encryption Model

### 17.1 Authentication Chain

```
Client в”Җв”ҖWSSв”Җв”Җв–¶ Envoy (TLS 1.3) в”Җв”Җв–¶ Gateway Pod
                                      в”Ӯ 1. Verify JWT (RS256)
                                      в”Ӯ 2. Check exp, iat, nbf
                                      в”Ӯ 3. Verify tokenVersion vs DB
                                      в”Ӯ 4. Check user != SUSPENDED
                                      в”Ӯ 5. IP reputation check
                                      в”Ӯ 6. Rate limit check
                                      в”Ӯ FAIL вҶ’ close(4401)
                                      в”Ӯ PASS вҶ’ connection established
```

### 17.2 Per-Call Authorization

**Existing implementation:** [call.authorization.ts](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/modules/call/call.authorization.ts)

Parallel checks: `block status` вҲҘ `privacy settings` вҲҘ `follow status` вҲҘ `spam score`

### 17.3 Additional Security

- **Replay prevention:** Nonce + timestamp + HMAC-SHA256 вҖ” [replay-guard.ts](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/modules/security/replay-guard.ts)
- **IP reputation:** Sorted set with exponential decay вҖ” [ip-reputation.ts](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/modules/security/ip-reputation.ts)
- **Rate limiting:** Per-event sliding window вҖ” [rate-limiter.ts](file:///d:/projects/social/backend/src/modules/security/rate-limiter.ts)
- **TURN security:** denied-peer-ip for RFC 1918 ranges, no anonymous allocations, 2 Mbps per-allocation cap
- **Payload limits:** SDP 10KB, ICE 1KB max

---

## 18. Failure Scenarios & Recovery

| Scenario | Detection | Response Time | Recovery |
|----------|-----------|--------------|----------|
| WS Gateway pod crash | K8s liveness probe | 10s | Auto-restart, Redis session intact, client reconnects |
| Redis shard failure | Sentinel failover | 5-15s | Replica promotion, clients retry |
| Full region outage | Route 53 health check | 30-60s | DNS failover вҶ’ nearest healthy region |
| TURN cluster overload | Custom metric >90% | 15s | Spill to adjacent region's TURN |
| Kafka broker failure | ISR shrinkage | 10s | Auto broker replacement |
| Network partition | Heartbeat failure | 30s | Call auditor reconciliation |
| 1M+ call spike in <60s | `call_initiations/s > 16K` | Immediate | HPA 10x, circuit breaker queues at 20K/s |
| ICE negotiation failure | 30s timeout | 30s | вҶ’ FAILED state, notify both users |
| Video upgrade conflict during reconnect | CAS conflict | Immediate | Reject upgrade, maintain audio |

### 18.1 Thundering Herd Prevention

Exponential backoff with full jitter: `delay = random() Г— min(base Г— 2^attempt, 30s)`

Staggered reconnect on pod termination: each client gets `retryAfterMs: 1000 + random() * 4000`

